V1.0: * First official release

V2.0: * Included wildcard support.
      * Better output.
      * Single-/multilibrary mode included.
      * Better error-checking (no more wobbly output!)
      * More accurate timing (using arexx's built-in functions instead of
        dos' date command).
      * ++

V2.1: * Kilobytes per second columns included.
      * Output uses self-adjusting columns.
      * Bugs removed from the CreateConfig-script.
      * More accurate timing : pack from disk to disk, unpack from disk to
        ram.


